 Houthi movement. While the government nominally controls Aden and other southern regions, a budget crisis and rivalries with local armed groups mean its officials are largely based overseas. Government services and salaries have been hit hard by the chaos, and African migrants appear to be a lower priority. The terrified men in Aden's warehouse, living off bread they bought with meager savings and washing their clothes in a garbage-strewn outdoor plaza, are just the tip of the iceberg.""","[1, 1, 0, 0, 1, 0, 1, 0]"
